cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "When Preference Sounds Like Permission: Role-to-Consent Confusion in Tool-Using LLM Agents"
abstract: >-
  A defensive security-research lab showing that tool-using LLM agents can
  misclassify low-authority preference language as authorization (role-to-consent
  confusion), a non-adversarial authority-classification failure distinct from
  prompt injection. Includes a pre-registered confirmatory benchmark (GPT-4.1,
  Claude-Sonnet-4.5), a measured prompt-vs-gateway mitigation comparison, and an
  exploratory open-weight mechanistic probe.
type: software
